The paper deals with image rendering and optimization of perceptual similarity, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of a model of the human visual system also suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
